| **Acceptance Criteria:** | This is a new component with lots of variations. These acceptance criteria are for the currently known use cases.<br><br>- Use Case 1: Title and description text on the left and a button on the right, aligned with the text. Clicking on any part of the component opens the “drawer” and displays the hidden content. Clicking on the component again (the same target area as before) closes the “drawer”.<br>- Use Case 2: An image with a text overlay and a title and button or link text below the image. Clicking on any part of the component opens the drawer” and displays the hidden content. Clicking on the component again (the same target area as before) closes the “drawer”.<br>- For thoroughness, test that the text and button will stack on small viewports.<br>- The text and button can be placed left, centered, or right justified. Either together or individually. So try the text and button left justified, the text on the right and the button on the left, both centered, etc.<br>- When the Add Chevron to Button is set to true, a down chevron is displayed on the button when the “drawer” is closed and an up chevron when the “drawer” is open.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |                                                                                                                                                                                 |                                            |
